cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision in the context of robotics, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on domain adaptation and deep learning suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The use of robots and the specific challenges of robot vision suggest that cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category. The use of deep learning suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category. The focus on adapting to different domains suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. Finally, the use of visual data suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely but still possible category.
